contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:58.475 --> 01:01.576
Tessa Riley. Is that your real name?

01:01.578 --> 01:03.879
Depends on who you ask.

01:03.881 --> 01:06.114
When your entire life
has been based on a lie,

01:06.116 --> 01:07.582
it's hard to know what's real.

01:07.584 --> 01:10.452
I'll take that as a yes.

01:10.454 --> 01:12.554
So, Tessa, how old are you?

01:12.556 --> 01:15.089
That's also up for debate.

01:15.091 --> 01:18.292
Perhaps you should go
directly to the source.

01:18.294 --> 01:20.228
Tell us, Mum.

01:20.230 --> 01:23.097
Was I a winter baby?

01:23.099 --> 01:24.566
13, 14?

01:24.568 --> 01:26.467
15.

01:26.469 --> 01:29.303
And where do your adoptive
parents think you are right now?

01:29.305 --> 01:31.339
Well, I have no idea.

01:31.341 --> 01:33.407
I haven't seen them in over a year.

01:33.409 --> 01:35.442
But Steven and Suzanne never seemed

01:35.444 --> 01:37.845
particularly interested
in my whereabouts,

01:37.847 --> 01:39.747
even as a child.

01:39.749 --> 01:44.150
Seems odd considering
how much they paid for me.

01:44.152 --> 01:45.519
Paid?

01:45.521 --> 01:48.321
My parents were desperate

01:48.323 --> 01:52.192
to curry favor with the Kensington Firm.

01:52.194 --> 01:54.194
So when Sybil Griffiths approached them

01:54.196 --> 01:56.329
with a 9-pound, 2-ounce problem,

01:56.331 --> 01:59.099
they were more than happy
to provide a solution.

02:00.869 --> 02:02.936
In cash.

02:06.208 --> 02:08.108
Where are Steve and Suzanne now?

02:08.110 --> 02:11.978
Back in Sheffield with the
rest of their nauseating brood,

02:11.980 --> 02:13.179
I supposed.

02:13.181 --> 02:17.283
So you've been on your own
and on the run for over a year?

02:17.285 --> 02:18.885
It speaks.

02:18.887 --> 02:21.387
- I don't buy it.
- Why is that?

02:21.389 --> 02:24.189
Because no 15 year old is
equipped to survive on her own.

02:24.191 --> 02:27.059
And you're not attractive enough
to have got by on your looks.

02:27.061 --> 02:28.694
You can't fight genetics.

02:28.696 --> 02:31.363
It is difficult to
imagine a 15-year-old girl

02:31.365 --> 02:33.899
doing what you've done all by herself.

02:33.901 --> 02:35.667
Nothing like plotting
your mother's death

02:35.669 --> 02:38.670
to keep a girl motivated.

02:38.672 --> 02:42.741
Still, you'd think you'd at
least want to meet your mother.

02:42.743 --> 02:44.209
Alleged mother.

02:44.211 --> 02:47.346
Before you killed her.

02:47.348 --> 02:50.348
Imagine growing up in a home

02:50.350 --> 02:54.820
where everyone despised
you but you had no idea why.

02:54.822 --> 02:57.662
And then one day you
discovered the truth,

02:57.665 --> 02:59.424
and suddenly it all makes sense.

02:59.426 --> 03:03.261
All the shame, the abuse, the pain.

03:05.432 --> 03:08.366
And there's a person

03:08.368 --> 03:12.337
responsible for all of it.

03:12.339 --> 03:16.174
You do some digging, you
find out she's a mobster,

03:16.176 --> 03:18.343
a murderer,

03:18.345 --> 03:21.946
a monster.

03:21.948 --> 03:24.014
You poor thing.

03:32.291 --> 03:34.725
I'm so sorry.

03:36.462 --> 03:38.962
You're absolutely right.

03:41.133 --> 03:43.400
I am a monster.

03:46.472 --> 03:49.239
Deal with these. Have them tested.

03:55.930 --> 04:00.711
